# üêû bug report
Hi, 
I'm submitting an issue with ChangeDetection when using AsyncPipe. Here is the [stackblitz](https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-change-detection-error) reproduction of the issue.
I can solve it by adding debounceTime(0) on my pipe, but it's not a good solution. 
I've also tried to subscribe to the observable in the component 'ts', it also solve the issue. This only happens when i use async Pipe.
### Affected Package
@angular/core

### Is this a regression?
No, i don't think so.
### Description
> Does reproduce the issue
app.component.html
```
<ng-container *ngIf="toto$ | async as obs">
  {{obs}}
  {{cssStyle}}
</ng-container>
```
app.component.ts
```
import { Component, OnInit, HostBinding } from '@angular/core';
import { BehaviorSubject } from 'rxjs';
import { tap, debounceTime } from 'rxjs/operators';

@Component({
  selector: 'my-app',
  templateUrl: './app.component.html',
  styleUrls: [ './app.component.css' ]
})
export class AppComponent implements OnInit {
  @HostBinding('attr.data-css')
  cssStyle = 'totoClass';
  
  obs$ = new BehaviorSubject<string>('initial value');
  toto$;

  ngOnInit() {
    setInterval(()=> {
      this.obs$.next('this must fail');
    }, 2000);
    this.toto$ = this.obs$.pipe(tap(val => this.cssStyle = 'newClass'));
  }
}
```
> Solve the issue, inconvenient we must handle unsubscribe
```
<ng-container *ngIf="obs">
  {{obs}}
  {{cssStyle}}
</ng-container>
```
app.component.ts
```
import { Component, OnInit, HostBinding } from '@angular/core';
import { BehaviorSubject } from 'rxjs';
import { tap, debounceTime } from 'rxjs/operators';

@Component({
  selector: 'my-app',
  templateUrl: './app.component.html',
  styleUrls: [ './app.component.css' ]
})
export class AppComponent implements OnInit {
  @HostBinding('attr.data-css')
  cssStyle = 'totoClass';
 
  obs$ = new BehaviorSubject<string>('initial value');
  obs: string;
  ngOnInit() {
    setInterval(()=> {
      this.obs$.next('this must fail');
    }, 2000);
    this.obs$.pipe(tap(val => this.cssStyle = 'newClass')).subscribe(val => this.obs = val);
  }
}
```
## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-change-detection-error

## üî• Exception or Error
<pre><code>
ERROR
Error: ExpressionChangedAfterItHasBeenCheckedError: Expression has changed after it was checked. Previous value: 'data-css: totoClass'. Current value: 'data-css: newClass'.
</code></pre>


